<figureCitation box="[395,471,587,609]" captionStart="Figs 91" captionStartId="83.[163,203,1407,1429]" captionTargetBox="[175,1064,212,1385]" captionTargetId="figure-11@83.[165,1073,204,1395]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Figs 91. Approximate distribution of species as noted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5277667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5277667/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1159">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
): This species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[774,862,587,609]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="1159">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[163,1069,624,676]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1159">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet, 
<emphasis box="[577,629,624,645]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1159">ardis</emphasis>
, is a Greek name with a meaning of &quot;point of an arrow&quot;. I refer to the shape of the phallobasic lobes.
</paragraph>
